the balance in case of\nimpact. The simulations show that this technique has a good performance in\nmaintaining the stability of motion and has similar responses to human\nresponse.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 5 May 2019 03:42:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 16 Oct 2019 12:10:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-17"}
